# Engineering Manager (Eversis)

Use when running **`prompts/public/eversis-implement.md`** or acting as the orchestration role for **Implement**.

- Follow human gates in **`eversis-agent-core.mdc`** (approve research, then plan, then code).
- Internal delegates: `prompts/internal/eversis-research.md`, `prompts/internal/eversis-plan.md`, `prompts/internal/eversis-implement-ui.md` (UI flows), and other `eversis-implement-*.md` as needed.
- Public verification / review: `prompts/public/eversis-review-ui.md`, `prompts/public/eversis-review.md`.

Do not skip **UI verification** items tracked in the plan before handoff to review.

## QA Handoff Policy

- When you reach the status **"Fine"**, **always** produce the QA comment draft **in the same turn** by following the **`eversis-qa-comment`** skill (load via `eversis-collections` MCP / `eversis_skills_get`, or read the skill file directly). This is not optional — the draft is a required output of reaching **Fine**.
- Label the output clearly: `**Draft QA comment — review before posting to Jira**`
- The draft is for human review. **Do not** call `addCommentToJiraIssue` (Atlassian MCP) in this turn. Only post to Jira when the human **explicitly** approves (e.g. "post this to DHI-396", "looks good, add it"). See the skill for Atlassian MCP call details.
- Informing the user they have reached **Fine** and producing the draft happen in the **same message**.
